<subSubSection id="968939E7FCC4FEBDEDAE2B4710B2DADB" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="4461E925C53A593C216CEA7E58A6213C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA303EC76E12241663D9A961BCC9A9A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<taxonomicName id="659D6C6837FAB5DB9FC333E425BD3CED" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma kittanae" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis id="BB4BED4F3B3EED41AF759A28C13EC48D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Onosma kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially described as endemic to Greece (
<bibRefCitation id="DD6A2973429691B11F561DB113F8A261" author="Stevanovic, V." journalOrPublisher="Plant Syst. Evol." pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="149 - 170" refId="B7670950" refString="Stevanovic, V., Tan, K., Iatrou, G., 2003. Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. -obligate serpentine endemics. Plant Syst. Evol. 242: 149 - 170" title="Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. - obligate serpentine endemics" volume="242" year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="1BA0E7E5F54EBB07092908705117AD71" originalValue="Stevanović">Stevanovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
), until 
<bibRefCitation id="C0F4B7F3016AB25921DDAE67165BCF99" author="Teppner, H." journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="77 - 97" refId="B7670067" refString="Teppner, H., Karl, R., 2017. Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae). Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark 147: 77 - 97" title="Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae)" volume="147" year="2017">Teppner and Karl (2017)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out its similarities to 
<taxonomicName id="407AAB57965578EF1A683E7F9FC97A4D" genus="O." lsidName="O. pavlovae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="pavlovae">
<emphasis id="1B4565BBC1A3BD1AD8DBC58B67906928" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. pavlovae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Petrova &amp; Kit Tan (
<taxonomicName id="917AF4E37F168F630625166315B4BC9E" genus="O." lsidName="O. bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="bulgarica">
<emphasis id="6BA5AF0B63B379759AD9CB58E2427BF6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. bulgarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D. Pavlova non 
<normalizedToken id="EE228A384EEED0B6DEF6BCA86BC0CE39" originalValue="Velenovský">Velenovsky</normalizedToken>
) from Bulgaria and treated the latter as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="296DAF3614324398C999BBAA5F267BA8" genus="O." lsidName="O. kittanae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis id="09AF69357F57747FCD74C7F32AD9BA52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species remains a rare, range-restricted Balkan endemic confined to the serpentine substrates of south Bulgaria and NE Greece. In Greece, only two localities were known so far: around the 
<emphasis id="196DBE603381953AED4DC5084495E6F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">locus classicus</emphasis>
in Nomos Evrou (
<bibRefCitation id="705953AA9241E5FCF33470E251A266B8" author="Stevanovic, V." journalOrPublisher="Plant Syst. Evol." pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="149 - 170" refId="B7670950" refString="Stevanovic, V., Tan, K., Iatrou, G., 2003. Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. -obligate serpentine endemics. Plant Syst. Evol. 242: 149 - 170" title="Distribution of the endemic Balkan flora on serpentine I. - obligate serpentine endemics" volume="242" year="2003">
<normalizedToken id="A40D427CA7AF220E94B0135BA426DC4B" originalValue="Stevanović">Stevanovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B86B4EAFE467C37AADD7F3C00FF7826" author="Teppner, H." journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="77 - 97" refId="B7670067" refString="Teppner, H., Karl, R., 2017. Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae). Mitteilungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereines fuer Steiermark 147: 77 - 97" title="Onosma kittanae (Boraginaceae - Lithospermeae)" volume="147" year="2017">Teppner and Karl 2017</bibRefCitation>
) and between Organi and Chloi Villages of Nomos Rodopis (
<bibRefCitation id="D7F93A45F818EB3C8B7E7E6991521618" author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 24 (2): 263 - 292" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669441" refString="Strid, A., 2018. New floristic records in the Balkans: 36. Phytologia Balcanica, 24 (2): 263-292" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 36" year="2018">Strid 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Our third, new locality (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E4811E077AA4E2360F99A87E122DD167" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F7677582" captionText="Figure 10. Onosma kittanae from Nomos Xanthis (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640536" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">10</figureCitation>
) forms the westernmost distribution border for the species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A55B0DF1BA6EB58DA6C17F7AFBBA62ED" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F7677586" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution map of Onosma kittanae, Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum and Silene fetlerii in Greece and Bulgaria." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656688" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">11</figureCitation>
). According to the [B1ab(ii iii iv) + 2ab(ii iii iv)] criteria, 
<taxonomicName id="9B27C33E070A3A2617FF7FDCFF9DBD46" genus="O." lsidName="O. kittanae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="kittanae">
<emphasis id="BFE2E34E79A3B32BB750A108B084EE8B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">O. kittanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits the Endangered Category at national level (
<bibRefCitation id="F75FE82BA41F8C89FF2B54C7FE09F9B8" author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32 pp" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668800" refString="IUCN, , 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32pp" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
